name: Argentina vs Canada
summary: Argentina advanced to the Copa America final after defeating Canada 1-0 in the semifinal. The match, which took place at MetLife Stadium in New Jersey, was a rematch of the two teams' encounter in the group stage, which Argentina won 3-0. Lionel Messi was in action for Argentina, and he helped set up the winning goal, which was scored by Lautaro Martinez. The victory for Argentina means that they will face Brazil in the final.

name: Joe Bonsall
summary: Joe Bonsall, a beloved tenor vocalist for the legendary country and gospel group the Oak Ridge Boys, passed away at the age of 76. Bonsall's five-decade tenure with the band made him a mainstay in the music industry. Sadly, his death was attributed to complications from amyotrophic lateral sclerosis (ALS). name: Alec Baldwin
summary: Alec Baldwin's trial for involuntary manslaughter in the 2021 "Rust" shooting has begun with jury selection finalized. The prosecution and defense will present their cases in the trial, which revolves around the discharge of a prop gun by Baldwin and the death of cinematographer Halyna Hutchins. A judge has ruled that Baldwin's role as co-producer of "Rust" is not relevant to the charges against him, which stem from his handling of the prop gun. The trial is expected to focus on the handling and safety protocols surrounding the prop gun, which was loaded with live ammunition. The outcome of the trial could have implications for the entertainment industry's safety procedures and standards.

name: United Airlines plane loses wheel
summary: A United Airlines Boeing aircraft has been forced to make an emergency landing in Denver after losing a wheel during takeoff from Los Angeles International Airport (LAX). The incident is the second time in four months that a United Airlines flight has lost a wheel during takeoff from LAX. The aircraft, which was carrying 131 passengers and six crew members, safely landed in Denver with no injuries reported. United Airlines has reported that the incident is under investigation by the airline and the National Transportation Safety Board (NTSB).

name: Jim Inhofe
summary: Former US Senator Jim Inhofe from Oklahoma passed away at the age of 89. During his long career, Inhofe was a staunch opponent of climate science, dismissing it as a "hoax" and actively working to discredit efforts to address climate change. His stance drew criticism from environmentalists and scientists, who highlighted the overwhelming scientific consensus on human-caused climate change. Inhofe also held strong views on defense and infrastructure, leaving a mark on Oklahoma and the national political landscape. His death has been met with both tributes and remembrances of his controversial legacy, particularly his positions on climate change denial.

name: Chicken recalled
summary: Multiple news sources are reporting a nationwide recall of over 2,000 pounds of Al-Safa frozen chicken products due to a listeria risk. The affected products include chicken kebabs and patties. Consumers are advised to discard any of these products they may have purchased and to thoroughly clean any surfaces that may have come into contact with them. Anyone who has consumed the recalled products and is experiencing symptoms of listeria, such as fever, muscle aches, nausea, vomiting, or diarrhea, should seek medical attention immediately. The recall is being issued by the United States Department of Agriculture's Food Safety and Inspection Service (FSIS).

name: CenterPoint outage map
summary: As Hurricane Beryl approaches the Texas coast, millions of residents are experiencing power outages. CenterPoint Energy's power outage map remains down, leaving Texans to seek alternative sources of information. The Austin American-Statesman and USA Today report that millions are without electricity, while Houston Public Media highlights the uncertainty surrounding restoration timelines. Forbes reports on the use of the Whataburger app to track power outages, as many Texans are turning to businesses for updates. Local news outlets such as FOX 26 Houston, KPRC Click2Houston, CW39 Houston, and KHOU.com provide live trackers and outage reporting platforms. CenterPoint Energy has announced that 1 million customers are expected to have power restored by the end of Wednesday.

name: Longlegs
summary: "Longlegs" has elicited a range of reactions from critics. Variety praises Nicolas Cage's performance as a serial killer who haunts viewers' nightmares, while Awards Radar hails it as a "serial killer horror masterpiece" that delves into viewers' psyches. We Live Entertainment notes Cage's "goodbye horses" moment, referencing his iconic performance in "Wild at Heart." JoBlo deems it a "very weird, very upsetting, thoroughly captivating horror show," while Nerdist finds it "a very flawed but creepy thriller." Jordan Ruimy recognizes its flaws but acknowledges its ability to "get under your skin." The Hollywood Reporter commends Maika Monroe and Cage's performances and its "satanic power." The Film Stage criticizes its "clean" procedural nature, and Forbes deems it "well-made nonsense." Lastly, IndieWire acknowledges its flaws but finds it a "disturbing fairy tale" that reveals the devil in plain sight.

name: Novak Djokovic
summary: Novak Djokovic, the Serbian tennis star, has expressed frustration with the Wimbledon crowd after reaching the quarterfinals. Djokovic accused some fans of disrespect and booing him during his match. In a post-match interview, he ridiculed the crowd, calling their behavior "disrespectful." Djokovic's comments have sparked controversy, with some supporting his stance while others criticize his reaction. Despite the controversy, Federer has expressed his admiration for Djokovic's achievements and hopes he can surpass Roger Federer's tennis records. Djokovic is now set to face Holger Rune, a rising Danish star, in the fourth round of Wimbledon. The match is expected to be close, with both players known for their aggressive style of play.

name: Jay Johnston
summary: Actor Jay Johnston, known for his roles in the animated series "Bob's Burgers" and the comedy film "Anchorman," has pleaded guilty to a felony charge stemming from his participation in the January 6, 2021 attack on the U.S. Capitol. According to reports, Johnston admitted to interfering with law enforcement officers during the riot, which disrupted the certification of the 2020 presidential election. The charges against him include one count of entering and remaining in a restricted building or grounds with the intent to impede or disrupt government business.

name: Houston
summary: Hurricane Beryl weakened to a tropical depression after making landfall in Texas as a Category 1 hurricane. The storm brought damaging winds and heavy rainfall, causing widespread power outages and at least four deaths. CenterPoint Energy, the main power provider in Houston, initially promised to restore power to one million customers by Wednesday, but their power outage map malfunctioned. Power outages remain a major concern for many residents, with nearly two million Houston-area customers still without electricity. The storm also caused the postponement of a soccer match between LAFC and Houston.

name: Freight
summary: There is a variety of news regarding freight transportation. In Fall River, freight trains will soon be operating on a night schedule as part of the South Coast Rail project. In Pennsylvania, a freight train derailed on a bridge over the Lehigh River. Meanwhile, the Freight House Farmers Market in Illinois has been temporarily relocated due to flooding. The state of California is considering a zero-emission train mandate that could impact freight nationwide. Elsewhere, there are reports, projects, and other news related to freight transportation outside of North America. In a legal matter, a former official of the Freight House Farmers' Market has received probation for embezzlement. Despite setbacks in the first quarter, Forward Air has appointed a permanent CFO. In the United Kingdom, plans are underway to convert a steam freight locomotive to hydrogen fuel. Additionally, Harbor Freight Tools is announcing the grand opening of a new store in North Dakota.

name: Ozone
summary: Air pollution, particularly ozone, remains a pressing environmental concern. The EPA is actively reviewing ozone standards to address its harmful effects. Summer airborne research is ongoing in the Rocky Mountains to study ozone pollution. Elevated ozone levels have prompted pollution advisories in Maricopa County, Arizona, and Phoenix. Researchers in Colorado are using various monitoring methods to identify sources of toxic ozone. Despite claims to the contrary, recent EPA regulations have not significantly impacted gas prices in Colorado. Additionally, New York City and several states are supporting the EPA's "Good Neighbor" rule, which aims to reduce ozone pollution from upwind states.
